Perform a public-facing redesign refactor that makes Xtrata look premium, exciting, and trustworthy, while preserving existing functionality and keeping admin tooling stable. The redesign must clearly communicate Xtrata’s unique value: open-source, chunked inscription protocol, mined transactions, deterministic reconstruction, sealing/immutability, and suitability as a Bitcoin-secured data layer replacing mutable off-chain references.

Hard Constraints

Do not break existing inscription/mint flows.

Keep admin screens and admin components working; minimal changes there.

Avoid large rewrites; prefer composition + wrappers.

Ensure the app remains fast: minimize rerenders, split bundles, lazy-load heavy screens.

Introduce a consistent design system (tokens, layout primitives), not ad-hoc CSS.

