Acceptance Criteria (definition of done)

Public site has consistent layout, nav, and typography across all key screens.

Trust Strip and protocol explainer appear in appropriate places.

Viewer and token cards look “premium” and are screenshot-worthy.

No admin regressions.

Lighthouse/perf checks show no major regressions.

All claims are factual and defensible (no “100x” unless substantiated in docs).

Optional but high value (if time allows)

Add “Activity” page that shows recent seals/mints in a clean timeline.

Add a “Protocol” page with the 3-step diagram and links to contract code.

Add “Verify” interactions (link to tx, show hashes, show seal state).

Tone / visual direction note for implementation

Aim for calm, architectural, inevitable.
Avoid neon gradients, meme energy, or over-animated UI.
Think “serious infrastructure with cultural weight”.